HEADWORD: Unatonable
<hw>Un`a*ton"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
capable of being brought into harmony; irreconcilable.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Unatonable</xex> matrimony.⟦rdquo⟧ <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being atoned for; inexpiable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unattached</ent>⟦br⟧
